Second Lady Karen Pence has been appointed as the Honorary Vice Chairwoman for Sister Cities International. In this role, she will promote the organization's mission of strengthening global relationships and advancing world peace. Mrs. Pence was honored by Sister Cities International in March with the Diplomatic Leadership Award for her contributions to American diplomacy. During her time as the First Lady of Indiana, she initiated cultural and educational exchanges to build and strengthen international relationships. Sister Cities International is a nonprofit organization founded by President Dwight D. Eisenhower in 1956, and it serves as a platform for citizen diplomacy efforts and knowledge-sharing.